# AGENT.md - Guidelines for agentic coding assistants

## Build & Development Commands
- Build: `pnpm build` (production), `pnpm build:local` (local with NO_HTTPS)
- Dev server: `pnpm dev` (uses turbopack)
- Type checking: `pnpm check-types`
- Lint: `pnpm lint` (next lint + biome), `pnpm lint:fix` (with auto-fix)
- Format: `pnpm format` (biome formatter)
- Test: `pnpm test` (run all tests), `pnpm test testname` (run single test)

## Code Style Guidelines
- TypeScript with strict types (except noImplicitAny: false)
- Use double quotes for strings (biome standard)
- 2 space indentation, LF line endings
- Line width: 90 characters max
- Imports are auto-organized by biome
- Use const by default, avoid var
- Paths aliases available: @/, ui/, app-types/, lib/, logger
- Error handling: Prefer typed errors with zod validation
- Naming: camelCase for variables/functions, PascalCase for components/types
- Components: Use React 19 with function components, hooks pattern
- State management: Primarily zustand
